A MAN sparked an armed siege after locking himself in a flat. Armed siege drama A MAN sparked an armed siege after locking himself in a flat.Dozens of police swooped on a quiet street in an Inverclyde town after the alarm was raised yesterday morning.Police Scotland confirmed officers were in attendance at Ashburn Gardens, Gourock, after being called to a report of a &quot;disturbance&quot;.Three vans of officers - who were carrying protective shields - were seen arriving at the incident at 10.30am.It is understood a man barricaded himself inside a flat in the street. Police said a 24-year-old man surrendered to officers shortly after 5pm and was taken to Inverclyde hospital for treatment.He was not arrested. 